<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-18614] Getting Route for a RouteConfiguration is null when doing manual route loading</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-18614</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I load the routeConfiguration like this:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
loader = extendedCamelContext.getRoutesLoader();
loader.loadRoutes(resource);&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#cc7832&quot;&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;font color=&quot;#172b4d&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;On a later moment, I like to remove or update the routeConfiguration, but I first want to check if it&apos;s already loaded. To do this, I try to get the route:&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;font color=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
&#160;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
List&amp;lt;Route&amp;gt; routes = context.getRoutes(); 
&#160;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;//or
&lt;/span&gt;
Route route = context.getRoute(id);
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&#160;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;font color=&quot;#172b4d&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;The route for the routeConfiguration is null and it&apos;s also not in the list. However when I would load it again it says &quot;RouteConfiguration ID already exists&quot;.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Version: Camel 3.18.2&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;JDK: 11 (Temurin)&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
