                            <comment id="17618036" author="davsclaus" created="Sat, 15 Oct 2022 08:00:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Can you add some more code to reproduce this - or some unit test etc&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17618885" author="skin27" created="Mon, 17 Oct 2022 13:00:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I attached the complete Class (RouteBuilder) that loads the routes, routeConfiguration and templatedRoutes. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;BTW: My initial idea to have an XML, something like&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;camel id=&quot;1234&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; &amp;lt;routes&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; &amp;lt;/routes&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; &amp;lt;routeConfigurations&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; &amp;lt;/routeConfiguration&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; &amp;lt;templatedRoutes&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; &amp;lt;/templateRoutes&amp;gt;&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; &amp;lt;dataFormats&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; &amp;lt;/dataFormats&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; &amp;lt;!-- etc --&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;/camel&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;And then&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
loader.loadOrUpdate(&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt; xml);&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Maybe the above will be available when this issues is solved:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-18189&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-18189&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;------------&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Until now, because the above use case isn&apos;t possible, I load them one by one with the routeLoader. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I want to use &quot;context.getRoute(&quot;id&quot;)&quot; to check if I need to use the load or update method. However this doesn&apos;t seems to cover all use cases. For example routeconfigurations doesn&apos;t work. This also seems to be the case when the route failes to load. On loading it again, the id is already loaded.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17625489" author="davsclaus" created="Fri, 28 Oct 2022 07:45:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;You need to use updateRoutes when updating&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
